# Tailwind CSS Conventions

## Class Organization

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Organize classes logically
<div className={`
  // Layout
  flex flex-col items-center justify-center
  // Spacing
  p-6 gap-4
  // Sizing
  w-full max-w-md min-h-screen
  // Colors & appearance
  bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-md
  // States
  hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow
  // Responsive
  md:p-8 md:max-w-lg
`}>
```

## Component Styling

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Use consistent spacing and sizing patterns
const cardStyles = {
  container: 'p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border',
  header: 'text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2',
  content: 'text-gray-700 leading-relaxed',
  button: 'px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors',
};

function FlashCard() {
  return (
    <div className={cardStyles.container}>
      <h3 className={cardStyles.header}>Question</h3>
      <p className={cardStyles.content}>Answer content</p>
      <button className={cardStyles.button}>Next Card</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Responsive Design

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Mobile-first responsive design
<div className={`
  // Mobile (default)
  grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 p-4
  // Tablet
  sm:grid-cols-2 sm:gap-6 sm:p-6
  // Desktop
  lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8 lg:p-8
  // Large desktop
  xl:grid-cols-4 xl:gap-10
`}>
```

## Dark Mode Support

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Include dark mode variants
<div className={`
  bg-white text-gray-900
  dark:bg-gray-900 dark:text-white
  border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700
`}>
```

## Animation & Transitions

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Smooth transitions for interactions
<button className={`
  transform transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out
  hover:scale-105 hover:shadow-md
  active:scale-95
  focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2
`}>
```

## Utility Patterns

- Use `space-y-*` for vertical spacing between children
- Use `divide-y` for borders between elements
- Prefer `text-*` over custom font sizes
- Use `ring-*` for focus states instead of `outline`